  "response_text": "Here's a simple and balanced one-day healthy meal plan that includes a variety of nutrients:\n\n### Breakfast:\n- **Oatmeal Bowl**\n  - 1/2 cup rolled oats cooked in water or almond milk\n  - Topped with:\n    - 1 tablespoon of almond butter\n    - 1/2 banana, sliced\n    - A sprinkle of cinnamon\n    - A handful of blueberries\n\n### Snack:\n- **Greek Yogurt Parfait**\n  - 1 cup plain Greek yogurt\n  - 1/4 cup granola (preferably low-sugar)\n  - 1/2 cup mixed berries (strawberries, raspberries, or blackberries)\n\n### Lunch:\n- **Quinoa Salad**\n  - 1 cup cooked quinoa\n  - 1/2 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n  - 1/2 cucumber, diced\n  - 1/4 cup red onion, finely chopped\n  - 1/4 cup feta cheese (optional)\n  - Dressing: 1 tablespoon olive oil, 1 tablespoon lemon juice, salt, and pepper to taste\n\n### Snack:\n- **Veggies and Hummus**\n  - Sliced bell peppers, carrots, and celery sticks\n  - 1/4 cup hummus for dipping\n\n### Dinner:\n- **Grilled Salmon with Vegetables**\n  - 4-6 oz. grilled salmon fillet\n  - Served with:\n    - 1 cup steamed broccoli\n    - 1/2 cup roasted sweet potatoes (drizzled with olive oil and seasoned with herbs)\n  \n### Dessert (optional):\n- **Chia Seed Pudding**\n  - 2 tablespoons chia seeds soaked in 1 cup almond milk overnight\n  - Sweetened with a drizzle of honey or maple syrup, and topped with a few slices of kiwi or mango.\n\n### Hydration:\n- Drink plenty of water throughout the day (aim for at least 8 cups) and feel free to include herbal teas or infused water for variety.\n\n### Notes:\n- Adjust portion sizes based on individual dietary needs and activity levels.\n- Feel free to swap out ingredients for personal preferences or dietary restrictions (e.g., use tofu or chicken instead of salmon, or choose different fruits and vegetables).\n- Aim for a balance of macronutrients (carbohydrates, proteins, and healthy fats) in meals throughout the day.\n\nThis meal plan provides a good mix of protein, healthy fats, and complex carbohydrates, along with plenty of vitamins and minerals from fruits and vegetables. Enjoy!",
